Lamar Odom of Lakers Wins Sixth Man Award as Best Reserve Player in NBA

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-04-20T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/lamar-odom-of-lakers-wins-sixth-man-award-as-best-reserve-payer-in-nba.html
Lamar Odom  of the  Los Angeles
Lakers  won the Sixth Man Award, given annually to the  National
Basketball Association â€™s best player in a reserve role.  Odom averaged 13 points and 7.5 rebounds this season while
coming off the bench in 47 games. He also started 35 games
because of injuries to players such as Andrew Bynum.  Odom, 31, received 513 of a possible 585 points from a
panel of 117 sports writers and broadcasters in  North America .
He got 96 first-place votes.  Jason Terry of the  Dallas Mavericks  got 244 points to
finish second for the second straight season. Thaddeus Young of
the  Philadelphia 76ers  was third, with 76 points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
